LUSAKA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Zambia on Saturday declared seven days of national mourning for its fourth President Rupiah Banda, who died on Friday at the age of 85 after battling colon cancer. Banda was in power from 2008 to 2011. Messages of condolences from leaders of other countries have started pouring in. Chushi Kasanda, the chief government spokesperson, told reporters that details of the former president's funeral will be made public in due course.  â– 